results.title: Little pink riding hood
abstracts: This story, inspired by the well-known classic, is about a greedy wolf who wants to eat a whole basket of cupcakes. He will have to face Little Pink Riding Hood, who confronts him with no fear. A story of kindness, courage, forgiveness and sharing. The book also encourages kids to play with their creativity and imagination, and create toys and costumes by reusing and recycling materials.

results.title: Bucky the dino goes green
abstracts: This is a story about Bucky, a big blue dinosaur who loves nature. One day, on his usual trip to the forest, his friend, Mr Robin, nearly choked on the wrapper that Bucky accidentally dropped on the ground. As he flies off and told Bucky "to go green", the learning starts on what it means and how everyone can play a part.

results.title: Breakfast with Lloyd & Liam
abstracts: Cory's younger twin brothers, Lloyd and Liam, are autistic and non-verbal. This is a heart warming story of the family having breakfast at the beach, and how Cory and his parents embrace the twins' special needs, staying positive and supportive of each other.

results.title: Little godwit finds his wings
abstracts: Little Godwit hatches late and finds out that his flock has left to escape the icy cold Arctic. Soon, he meets different birds and tries to fit in with them. Little Godwit has to decide if he would like to stay with these birds or keep flying.

results.title: Do farts make old people go faster?
abstracts: This is part of the series "Jack is curious". Jack, a curious boy, has an idea when his mother explains that Jack is hearing gas escaping from old people when they are farting.

results.title: The yummiest cupcake
abstracts: This children story revolves around Alex and his love of cupcakes. Being only allowed just one cupcake, Alex cannot make his mind up on which cupcake to choose for his birthday. Disappointed Alex receives a pleasant surprise upon getting home. The book also contains various cupcake recipes.

results.title: Can I hit back at a bully?
abstracts: Jack and his best friend Zac are at the playground when three bullies steal their football and call them mean names. Jack wants to use taekwondo to hit back at the bullies but his mother has other idea.

results.title: What a scare!
abstracts: One night Jeremy mistakes Rubiah for a ghost when she was having her pre-dawn meal for Ramadan. The next day Rubiah and Jeremy investigate odd "ghost" noises in the house. This book is about overcoming fears and cultural exchange.

results.title: The marvellous sugee cake
abstracts: This is a story about Simon, a seven years old boy and things that happened on his seventh birthday.

results.title: Meet the Wolols : welcome to Wololand
abstracts: This book is about Wolos, a group of joyful characters who aim to engage and encourage kids to play with their creativity and imagination, and create toys and costumes by reusing and recycling materials.

results.title: Make a wish for a unicorn : a book for little girls (and big girls too)
abstracts: This is an interactive picture book to promote imagination and helps children bond with their caregivers and each other by bringing play into reading to help improves their social well-being and learn how to follow instructions, problem-solve, speak with clarity and manage their emotions.

results.title: Ace agent Spycat and the flying sidekick
abstracts: Spycat is an ace agent extraordinaire from FELINE, a crime-fighting organisation. His latest mission is to investigate and stop the evil penguin king Blackwing who has turned the tropical island of Boracay into his own frozen paradise. But first, Spycat must learn to work together with his new partner, junior agent Rockcat.

results.title: Pinto's pinky promises
abstracts: Pinto loves making pinky promises, but he fails to keep his promises! Pinto apologises to his friends, and makes a pinky promise to make it up to them.

results.title: Saturday's surprisingly super-duper lesson
abstracts: Aish is bored doing maths problems in a classroom on a Saturday morning and she begins to doodle. The drawings come to life and soon the whole class is bubbled over with ideas to create a fantastical roller coaster. This is a tale that showcases and encourages creativity.

results.title: My BFF is an alien
abstracts: This is a story about two thirteen-year-old classmates one of whom is an alien. The efforts of two girls who are the best of friends to find a precious element needed to power the alien's family spaceship are thwarted by their mean classmates.

results.title: Theodore and the lady in the purple dress
abstracts: This story tells of the adventures of Theodore, a teddy bear. Theodore was having fun at the fair until he was left behind by Annabelle on a ferris wheel. While trying to find his way home, Theodore came to a shop selling children's clothes and toys. There he saw Annabelle and her parents leaving the shop without Annabelle's baby brother, Brian. Follow Theodore as he tries to rescue baby Brian from being taken by the Lady in the purple dress.

results.title: Mummy loves me
abstracts: This is a book on mother's love. For beginning readers it assures children of their mothers' unconditional love.

results.title: Out of order
abstracts: Professor Plano, Zed and Zee find themselves in Lord Myopic's Machiville, a place run by machines. When these machines revolt, Professor Plano and the boys have to figure out how to get the citizens of Machiville out of danger.

results.title: Make animals great again : and other creature campaigns
abstracts: In this children's story, the older animals of Singapore are worried about the deteriorating values of the Next Generation. The animals agree a new leader of the Animal Council is needed to address the issue.

results.title: Kelly and the Krumps
abstracts: This is a story about a teen beset with academic pressures and technology overload. Kelly Mao has got quite the headache: tiger mum, endless tuitions, PSLE, dancing, and her twin brother's troubles with a secret online gaming centre!

results.title: The royal pup pack : party at the palace
abstracts: Written in honour of Prince Louis on his first birthday and Archie Harrison's arrival, the book celebrates the British royal pup pack of Lupo, Guy, Oz and Jack. Follow the adventures of these royal pups at Prince Louis' first birthday party.

results.title: The brilliant oil lamp
abstracts: Asha and her family move to a housing estate in Toa Payoh and they use an oil lamp to bless their new home. When the power goes out, Asha discovers how the lamp's brilliant light comes in handy, and brings new and old friends together.

results.title: To Japan, with love : a collection of short stories inspired by a visit to Japan
abstracts: National Book Development Council Singapore staff and 23 writing/illustration students from Hwa Chong Institute, LASALLE College of the Arts, Nanyang Academy of Fine Arts, Singapore Polytechnic, School of the Arts, Singapore, and Temasek Polytechnic visited Tokyo and Hakuba Village, Nagano Prefecture in Japan from 13-20 December 2016. In a three-hour workshop for the Japanese and Singapore students popular children’s stories in both countries were shared and new story ideas created. This book is the result of the ideas of the Singaporean students.

results.title: One fine day there was a frog
abstracts: This is a storybook written by author Terry Moran, for young readers. The story is written in rhymes, with accompanying colourful illustrations. This story is about a frog which invited other animals to tea.

results.title: A man on the moon
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who imagines herself seeing a man on the moon.

results.title: The fun farm
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a farm which provides fun activities for visitors.

results.title: Sue and her blue shoes
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who was stuck in a patch of glue on her way to school.

results.title: A snail in a pail
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for young readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who kept a snail in a pail.

results.title: Little Baby Bob
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a baby who loves to play with pots.

results.title: A star in a jar
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who dreamt that she had a star in a jar.

results.title: Jay, Clay and Ray
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about how a boy with a limp manages to make friends with another boy who keeps bullying him.

results.title: The big fat cat
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a cat and a rat.

results.title: The little toy shop
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about how a boy manages to get a policeman to catch a robber who has robbed a toy shop.

results.title: Counting numbers 1 to 10
abstracts: Counting penguins. Sing the penguins song. One little two little three little penguins. Counting backwards from 10 to 1. This is a happy counting book for preschool children.

results.title: Water buffalo's reward
abstracts: This is a children's story on a water buffalo who learns that diligence will bring about a bountiful harvest.

results.title: Secrets of Singapore : National Gallery
abstracts: This book offers art-related information such as the various art venues in Singapore, tips on how to appreciate art and well-known Singapore artists. Readers can also join Professor Brushie and Curious Canvas in discovering the fascinating facts and history of National Gallery Singapore, such as secret passages, hidden dome and chocolate ceiling.

results.title: Wagga learns about COVID-19
abstracts: This book contains two parts. In the first part, Wagga learns about COVID-19 and how to fight it. In the second part, upset at being unable to go out often, Wagga learns how to cope with his anger and comes up with a "stay at home" plan.

results.title: Chop-chop the trishaw
abstracts: Chop-chop the trishaw gets an engine and is now able to zoom fast like the other vehicles. But this does not make Chop-chop happy, so it decides to have the engine removed and goes back to being its old "slow" self.

results.title: The secret of the Tiger's Den
abstracts: The Sengkang Snoopers and their loyal feathered sidekick are having a staycation at Sentosa, and stumble upon a mystery that lands them into mortal danger. Is there a hidden treasure from the Japanese Occupation? Following a harrowing trail that leads them to Tiger's Den, the gang is determined to find out.

results.title: Lion boys and fan girls
abstracts: This is the sequel to "Lion boy and drummer girl". It is a story about Lion Legends, a lion dance troupe. The troupe finds itself a victim of cyberbullying and then a garbage bomb.

results.title: Yaya the double-decker bus
abstracts: This children's fiction book is about Yaya, the best bus in the country. He is very arrogant that he is number one in speed, looks and height until proven that he cannot do everything.

results.title: Bubble kye
abstracts: Six Tions from planet Tionion. Their mission is to experience life on Earth. This time, Kye, one of the six, tries bubble gum for the first time with unexpected consequences.

results.title: Here we go : let the adventures begin!
abstracts: Six Tions from planet Tionion. Their mission is to experience life on Earth. In this book, the six, Jade, Kye, Indil, Joan, Lara and Ashi discover similarities and differences between Tionions and humans.

results.title: The bad beginning / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: After the sudden death of their parents, the three Baudelaire children must depend on each other and their wits when it turns out that the distant relative who is appointed their guardian is determined to use any means necessary to get their fortune.

results.title: The penultimate peril / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: In this next-to-last chronicle of the lives of the Baudelaire orphans, the siblings pose as concierges at the Hotel Denouement to learn the identities and intentions of certain enemies, encounter characters from their past adventures, and ponder the nature of nobility and villainy.

results.title: Morgain's revenge / Laura Anne Gilman.
abstracts: The quest for the Holy Grail is postponed again when Ailis is kidnapped by Morgain the sorceress, and her friends, Newt and Gerard, must leave the court of King Arthur seeking to rescue her, accompanied by a grumbling knight.

results.title: Long shot [electronic resource] / Timothy Tocher.
abstracts: When her father accepts a job as girls' basketball coach in another town, fifth-grader Laurie reluctantly leaves old friends and teammates and faces new challenges with a new basketball team at a new school.

results.title: Long shot [electronic resource] / Timothy Tocher.
abstracts: When her father accepts a job as girls' basketball coach in another town, fifth-grader Laurie reluctantly leaves old friends and teammates and faces new challenges with a new basketball team at a new school.

results.title: The Alamo cat [electronic resource] / written and illustrated by Rita Kerr.
abstracts: Recounts the adventures of Ruby, a stray kitten adopted by the patrol rangers at the Alamo as their mascot.

results.title: The shadow companion / Laura Anne Gilman.
abstracts: In the final book of the Grail Quest trilogy, Ailis, Newt, and Gerard join the quest for the Holy Grail and encounter the dark force that has been threatening them all along.

results.title: Sometimey friend [electronic resource] / Pansie Hart Flood ; illustrated by Felicia Marshall.
abstracts: When her mother goes to Florida in 1978, ten-year-old Sylvia stays behind in South Carolina, but when she fails to make new friends at school, she realizes that her newly-discovered great-grandmother and best friend, Miz Lula Maye, might be the problem.

results.title: Mallory on board [electronic resource] / by Laurie Friedman ; illustrations by Barbara Pollak.
abstracts: Despite her fears of being a "third wheel," Mallory goes on a cruise for the wedding of the mother and father of her two best friends.

results.title: Secret holes [electronic resource] / by Pansie Hart Flood ; illustrated by Felicia Marshall.
abstracts: Ten-year-old Sylvia has just discovered that her centenarian best friend is also her great-grandmother, and together they pursue discoveries yet to come.

results.title: Mallory on board [electronic resource] / by Laurie Friedman ; illustrations by Barbara Pollak.
abstracts: Despite her fears of being a "third wheel," Mallory goes on a cruise for the wedding of the mother and father of her two best friends.

abstracts: When her mother goes to Florida in 1978, ten-year-old Sylvia stays behind in South Carolina, but when she fails to make new friends at school, she realizes that her newly-discovered great-grandmother and best friend, Miz Lula Maye, might be the problem.

results.title: The reptile room / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: Violet, Klaus, and Sunny Baudelaire are intelligent children. They are charming, and resourceful, and have pleasant facial features. Unfortunately, they are exceptionally unlucky. In the first two books alone, the three youngsters encounter a greedy and repulsive villain, itchy clothing, a disastrous fire, a plot to steal their fortune, a lumpy bed, a deadly serpent, a large brass reading lamp, a long knife, and a terrible odour. In the tradition of great storytellers, from Dickens to Dahl, comes an exquisitely dark comedy that is both literary and irreverent, hilarious and deftly crafted. Never before has a tale of three likeable and unfortunate children been quite so enchanting, or quite so uproariously unhappy.

results.title: The end / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: Lost at sea, the Baudelaire orphans, along with the evil Count Olaf, wash up on the shore of an island populated by an oddly placid group of inhabitants, and they try to decide whether or not they are truly safe. Like an off-key violin concert, the Roman Empire, or food poisoning, all things must come to an end. Thankfully, this includes A Series of Unfortunate Events by Lemony Snicket. The thirteenth and final installment in the groundbreaking series will answer readers' most burning questions: Will Count Olaf prevail? Will the Baudelaires survive? Will the series end happily? If there's nothing out there, what was that noise? Then again, why trouble yourself with unfortunate resolutions? Avoid the thirteenth and final book of Lemony Snicket's international bestselling series and you'll never have to know what happens.

results.title: The perfect shot [electronic resource] / Elaine Marie Alphin.
abstracts: Brian uses basketball to block out memories of his girlfriend and her family who were gunned down a year ago, but the upcoming murder trial and a high school history assignment force him to face the past and decide how far he should go to see justice served. Includes facts about miscarriages of justice in American history.

results.title: Julie the rockhound [electronic resource] / by Gail Langer Karwoski ; illustrated by Lisa Downey.
abstracts: When a young girl finds a shiny quartz crystal, her dad shows her how to dig for minerals, and she becomes Julie the Rockhound. Includes "For Creative Minds" section.

abstracts: Originally published in East Orange, NJ by Just Us Books in 1998.

abstracts: Anne, an eleven-year-old orphan, is sent by mistake to live with a lonely, middle-aged brother and sister on a Prince Edward Island farm and proceeds to make an indelible impression on everyone around her.

results.title: Anne of Green Gables [electronic resource] / Lucy Maud Montgomery.
abstracts: Anne, an eleven-year-old orphan, is sent by mistake to live with a lonely, middle-aged brother and sister on a Prince Edward Island farm and proceeds to make an indelible impression on everyone around her.

results.title: The slippery slope / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: Like bad smells, uninvited weekend guests or very old eggs, there are some things that ought to be avoided. Snicket's saga about the charming, intelligent, and grossly unlucky Baudelaire orphans continues to alarm its distressed and suspicious fans the world over. The 10th book in this outrageous publishing effort features more than the usual dose of distressing details, such as snow gnats, an organised troupe of youngsters, an evil villain with a dastardly plan, a secret headquarters and some dangerous antics you should not try at home. With the weather turning colder, this is one chilling book you would be better off without.

results.title: The vile village / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: Dear Reader, You have undoubtedly picked up this book by mistake, so please put it down. Nobody in their right mind would read this particular book about the lives of Violet, Klaus, and Sunny Baudelaire on purpose, because each dismal moment of their stay in the village of V.F.D. has been faithfully and dreadfully recorded in these pages. I can think of no single reason why anyone would want to open a book containing such unpleasant matters as migrating crows, an angry mob, a newspaper headline, the arrest of innocent people, the Deluxe Cell, and some very strange hats. It is my solemn and sacred occupation to research each detail of the Baudelaire children's lives and write them all down, but you may prefer to do some other solemn and sacred thing, such as reading another book instead. With all due respect, Lemony Snicket.

results.title: Senderos fronterizos [electronic resource] / Francisco Jiménez.
abstracts: Having come from Mexico to California ten years ago, fourteen-year-old Francisco is still working in the fields but fighting to improve his life and complete his education.

results.title: The austere academy / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: As their outrageous misfortune continues, the Baudelaire orphans are shipped off to a miserable boarding school, Prufrock Preparatory School. They can't help but notice the enormous stone arch bearing the school's motto Memento Mori or "Remember you will die". This is not a cheerful greeting and certainly marks an inauspicious beginning to a very bleak story. They befriend the two Quagmire triplets and find that they have been followed by the dreaded Count Olaf.

results.title: The carnivorous carnival / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: On the run as suspected murderers, the unlucky Baudelaire orphans find themselves trapped in the Caligari Carnival, where they must masquerade as freaks in order to hide from the evil Count Olaf.

results.title: The grim grotto / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: The intrepid siblings delve further into the dark mystery surrounding the death of their parents and the baffling VFD organisation. Still pursued by the evil Count Olaf, the Baudelaire orphans attempt to reach a very important VFD meeting, but first they must travel in a rattletrap submarine to the Gorgonian Grotto, a dangerous underwater cave, in search of the sugar bowl.

results.title: The ersatz elevator / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: In their most daring misadventure, the Baudelaire orphans are adopted by very, very rich people, whose penthouse apartment is located mysteriously close to the place where all their misfortune began. Even though their new home in the city is fancy, and the children are clever and charming, I'm sorry to say that still, the unlucky orphans will encounter more disaster and woe. In fact, in this sixth book in A Series of Unfortunate Events, the children will experience a darkened staircase, a red herring, an auction, parsley soda, some friends in a dire situation, a secret passageway, and pinstripe suits.

results.title: The wide window / by Lemony Snicket ; illustrations by Brett Helquist.
abstracts: Dear Reader, If you have not read anything about the Baudelaire orphans, then before you read even one more sentence, you should know this: Violet, Klaus, and Sunny are kind-hearted and quick-witted, but their lives, I am sorry to say, are filled with bad luck and misery. All of the stories about these three children are unhappy and wretched, and this one may be the worst of them all. If you haven't got the stomach for a story that includes a hurricane, a signalling device, hungry leeches, cold cucumber soup, a horrible villain, and a doll named Pretty Penny, then this book will probably fill you with despair. I will continue to record these tragic tales, for that is what I do. You, however, should decide for yourself whether you can possibly endure this miserable story. With all due respect, Lemony Snicket.

results.title: Alien encounter [electronic resource] / Pamela F. Service ; illustrated by Mike Gorman.
abstracts: Alien agent Zack travels to Roswell, New Mexico, to search for an alien boy who's stolen a space ship in order to find his missing father, who crashed near Roswell in 1947.

results.title: Who what wear / Olivia Bennett ; illustrated by Georgia Rucker.
abstracts: "Emma Rose is SO not famous. So how did she score inside information on the most talked-about party of the year? Because Emma is secretly the hottest new fashion designer-Allegra Biscotti-and hired to whip up a Sweet Sixteen dress for the guest of honor. Wait-- fashion emergency! How can she create a fiercely fashionable dress and keep her secret? There's only one solution: Emma must go undercover-as her own intern! But when Emma feels the pressure by her BFF to explain how she got an invite from the in-crowd and an ultra-fabulous fashion internship-just when Jackson finally starts paying attention to her-she knows she has to make it work--or will it all come apart at the seams?"--Page 4 of cover.

abstracts: After moving to a new town, eight-year-old Mallory keeps throwing stones in the "Wishing Pond" but things will not go back to the way they were before, and she remains torn between old and new best friends.

results.title: Almost to freedom [electronic resource] / by Vaunda Micheaux Nelson ; illustrations by Colin Bootman.
abstracts: Tells the story of a young girl's dramatic escape from slavery via the Underground Railroad, from the perspective of her beloved rag doll.

abstracts: While buying gifts for his family to wear to the mosque on Eid a shoemaker is persuaded to get new pants for himself, but the only pair available is too long and no one seems to have time to shorten them.

results.title: The red shoe [electronic resource] / Ursula Dubosarsky.
abstracts: Three sisters growing up in post-World War II Sydney, Australia, deal with their mentally unstable father, their possibly unfaithful mother, and the defecting Russian spy who lives next door.

results.title: City witch, country switch [electronic resource] / by Wendy Wax ; illustrated by Scott Gibala-Broxholm.
abstracts: While paying a surprise visit to her city-dwelling cousin, Muffletump misses her home in the country but when Mitzi leaves the city to see where Muffletump lives, she is just as uncomfortable until the two, together, conjure a solution.

abstracts: With the lantern festival close at hand, Old Chan, the master paper lantern maker, must find an apprentice with the talent to continue his work.
